<body>
    <h1>SSB Deployment Guide</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p><strong>Standard Services Build</strong></p>
<p>Standard Services Build<strong> </strong>&nbsp;is a set of predefined co=
nfigurations and best practices provided by SailPoint to streamline identit=
y governance deployments. SSB helps organizations implement identity securi=
ty solutions more efficiently by offering standardized workflows, rules, an=
d policies that align with common use cases.</p>
<p>The <strong>Standard Services Build (SSB)</strong> in <strong>SailPoint =
</strong>offers several advantages, making identity governance deployments =
more efficient and effective. Here are the key benefits:</p>
<h3 id=3D"SSBDeploymentGuide-1.FasterImplementation"><strong>1. Faster Impl=
ementation</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Predefined configurations and best practices reduce deployment time.</p>=
</li>
<li>
<p>Minimizes the need for custom development, leading to quicker go-live.</=
p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"SSBDeploymentGuide-2.Standardization&amp;BestPractices"><strong>2=
. Standardization &amp; Best Practices</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Ensures consistency across identity governance processes.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Reduces risks by following SailPoint-recommended configurations.</p></li=
>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"SSBDeploymentGuide-3.ReducedComplexity"><strong>3. Reduced Comple=
xity</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Simplifies identity lifecycle management with ready-to-use workflows.</p=
></li>
<li>
<p>Eliminates the need for extensive customization, reducing maintenance ef=
forts.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"SSBDeploymentGuide-4.CostEfficiency"><strong>4. Cost Efficiency</=
strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Lowers implementation costs by reducing development and consulting effor=
ts.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Reduces long-term maintenance and support costs.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"SSBDeploymentGuide-5.EnhancedSecurity&amp;Compliance"><strong>5. =
Enhanced Security &amp; Compliance</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Built-in compliance controls align with industry standards.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Reduces security risks by enforcing identity governance best practices.<=
/p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"SSBDeploymentGuide-6.Scalability&amp;Flexibility"><strong>6. Scal=
ability &amp; Flexibility</strong></h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Provides a solid foundation that can be expanded based on business needs=
.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Supports future enhancements without requiring major redesigns.</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Currently we are deploying the changes manually every two weeks. The lon=
g term goal is to replace the manual effort and introduce the SSB process. =
Before we start the build process the following steps have been taken to st=
andardize the repository.</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Standardized Object Naming Convention</strong> to improve consis=
tency and maintainability.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Optimized Configuration Management</strong> by updating dynamic =
values with tokenized placeholders in XML files.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Enhanced Environment-Specific Configurations</strong> by updatin=
g <code>Dev.target.properties</code>, <code>Uat.target.properties</code>, a=
nd <code>Prod.target.properties</code> with appropriate tokens.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Streamlined Token Utilization</strong> by removing unused or emp=
ty-value tokens.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Eliminated Redundant Files</strong> by deleting duplicate XML an=
d junk files from the bundle object.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Ensured Configuration Accuracy</strong> by executing Ant command=
s to replace tokens with correct values.</p></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Steps to implement SSB process:</strong></p>
<ol start=3D"1">
<li>
<p>Download SSB from compass and Unzip</p></li>
